<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-15T12:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-15T12:40:00-05:00" n="1165" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1165">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4933.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo
                                    Laredo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-15T11:00:00-06:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have found that a simultaneous uprising has been planned at Mexico
                            City, Puebla, San Luis Potosí, Saltillo, Monterey, and probably other of
                            the principal cities. It includes also the turning of the entire Federal
                            army in northern Mexico from Madero, including General Huerta, who will
                            be commander in chief of the new rebel army, with Orozco second in
                            command.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>